{"key":"processedPost-13272169","value":{"id":13272169,"first":13267138,"last":13276926,"when":1285899029,"utime":"10/01/10 05:10 AM","content":"You want to make sure the grain spawn is <i>fully colonized</i>, period.&nbsp; Beyond that, there's no need to wait, but bear in mind, the very first 'fuzzies' on grain do not indicate full colonization.&nbsp; Full colonization is when the grains are fully 'white'.<br /><br />We use the term <i>consolidation</i> with regards to fruiting substrates to give them time to actually digest part or most of the substrate before introducing to fruiting conditions.&nbsp; Doing this with grain spawn is actually counter-productive because you want to use your spawn while the mycelium is still rapidly expanding.<br /><br />I suspect the OPs problem is either contaminated grains or failure to properly pasteurize the bulk substrate material.<br />RR","title":"Re: cotaims?"}}